SectionProjectChallenges.part1Text: It is not enough to build sustainable energy production, the project and the organization are also expected to be sustainable (social, environmental, economic)
SectionProjectChallenges.part3Text: The energy industry should only be fossil-free 2045 Local resistance increasingly tough Permit processes - x% (more and more) get rejected) - together we can reverse the trend / catch up
SectionProjectContact.textLineOne: Free installation for members of Swedish Wind Energy. *
SectionProjectFAQ.Title2: What projects is Medla used for?
SectionProjectFAQ.Title3: Is it easy to get started?
SectionProjectFAQ.Title4: Do we need to adapt our approach to Medla?
SectionProjectFAQ.Title7: Which vendors can track our projects?
SectionProjectFAQ.Title8: Does Medla have any binding time?
SectionProjectFAQ.Title9: We have projects in another business platform, how does Medla work then?
SectionProjectFAQ.Title10: Can projects outside Sweden be connected?
SectionProjectFAQ.Text1: Designers who want to lift profits and anchor their projects, construction contractors who need goods and services in projects and local businesses that want to deliver to the energy industry.
SectionProjectFAQ.Text2: Green industrial projects in all design phases.
SectionProjectFAQ.Text3: Getting started with Medla is easy. After you contact us, we confirm your project details and install the projects in 1-2 weeks. Based on project status, we hold introductions for the project contractor and local stakeholders.
SectionProjectFAQ.Text4: No. Medla facilitates the work you already do and contributes to increased local benefit - without you having to change your working methods.
SectionProjectFAQ.Text5: Prices depend on the status, size and number of projects that are connected. Medla has no commitment period and you keep the supplier list if you choose to cancel a project.
SectionProjectFAQ.Text6: Saved time in project communication, more local jobs as a result of your project, measurable results on the local community benefit from your projects.
SectionProjectFAQ.Text7: All vendors that meet Medla's Terms of Use, and are not blacklisted by you.
SectionProjectFAQ.Text8: Medla has no lock-in period, termination will be executed at the next payment.
SectionProjectFAQ.Text9: The connection to Medla is made per project and can therefore be used in addition to other business platforms. If you want to move your entire project portfolio to Medla, we can help you with that.
SectionProjectFAQ.Text10: It is possible to connect projects outside Sweden, we update the language support for new regions if necessary.
SectionMunicipalityFAQ.Title2: What projects is Medla used for?
SectionMunicipalityFAQ.Title3: Is it easy to get started?
SectionMunicipalityFAQ.Title8: Does Medla have any binding period?
SectionMunicipalityFAQ.Title9: We have projects in another business platform, how does Medla work then?
SectionMunicipalityFAQ.Title10: Can projects outside Sweden be connected?
SectionMunicipalityFAQ.Text1: Municipalities that want to show and make their business more accessible, planners who want to lift profits and anchor their establishments, construction companies that need goods and services in projects and local businesses that want to deliver to the projects.
SectionMunicipalityFAQ.Text2: Sustainable energy and industrial projects in all phases (wind farms, solar parks, hydrogen plants, battery factories, green steel projects and many more)
SectionMunicipalityFAQ.Text3: Getting started with Medla is easy. After you have contacted us, we will confirm your information and install the municipal page in 1-2 weeks.
SectionMunicipalityFAQ.Text4: Projects are connected continuously, when a project connects in your region, their project page will be visible via your municipality page.
SectionMunicipalityFAQ.Text5: Prices depend on the size of the municipality. Medla has no lock-in period and you keep the business register even if you cancel.
SectionMunicipalityFAQ.Text6: Better inventoried business, improved business opportunities for business and a more attractive municipality for investment.
SectionMunicipalityFAQ.Text7: Affiliate projects are displayed with a project page where their jobs and needs are advertised.
SectionMunicipalityFAQ.Text8: Medla has no lock-in period, termination will be executed at the next payment.
SectionMunicipalityFAQ.Text9: The connection to Medla is made per project and can therefore be used in addition to other business platforms. If you want to move your entire project portfolio to Medla, we can help you with that.
SectionMunicipalityFAQ.Text10: It is possible to connect projects outside Sweden, we update the language support for new regions if necessary.
SectionCompanyFAQ.Title2: What projects is Medla used for?
SectionCompanyFAQ.Title3: Is it easy to get started?
SectionCompanyFAQ.Title4: How can Medla be free for small businesses?
SectionCompanyFAQ.Title6: What types of jobs are available at Medla?
SectionCompanyFAQ.Title7: How do I find the jobs?
SectionCompanyFAQ.Title8: Can I track multiple projects with the same account?
SectionCompanyFAQ.Text1: Municipalities that want to show and make their business more accessible, designers who want to lift profits and anchor their establishments, construction companies that need goods and services in projects and local businesses that want to deliver to the projects.
SectionCompanyFAQ.Text2: Sustainable energy and industrial projects in all phases (wind farms, solar parks, hydrogen plants, battery factories, green steel projects and many more)
SectionCompanyFAQ.Text3: It only takes a couple of minutes, register your business and choose which projects and industries are relevant to you.
SectionCompanyFAQ.Text4: Medla's main business model lies with municipalities and project owners.
SectionCompanyFAQ.Text5: For small businesses, Medla will always be free.
SectionCompanyFAQ.Text6: All project needs can be set up, everything from construction work in the workplace to indirect needs such as catering, hairdressing services and leisure activities.
SectionCompanyFAQ.Text7: After registration you can see all jobs on Medla, jobs are displayed in our search function which you can easily find at the top of the website.
SectionCompanyFAQ.Text8: Yes, at Medla you register once and then easily select the projects where you want to be seen and get job notices.

SectionWhatIsMedla.part3Text: Apply to connect your project to Medla {connectProject}. For questions or concerns {mailTo}.
SectionWhatIsMedla.titleLineOne: Built with the industry, for the industry.
SectionWhatIsMedlaDescription.Title3: Everything gathered on your project page
SectionWhatIsMedlaDescription.Text1: Invite, search and compare project local vendors - they register themselves and are controlled by Medla.
SectionWhatIsMedlaDescription.Text2: Publish project needs (as simple as sending an SMS) and get responses from relevant vendors - we make it just as easy for your contract.
SectionWhatIsMedlaDescription.Text3: Local business, job opportunities and project information on unique Medla domain.
SectionWhatIsMedlaDescription.Text4: See the number of mediated transactions and measure the local impact of the project.
SectionWhatIsMedlaDescriptionMunicipalit: Company Profiles, Quotation Requests, Notices and Messaging Features.
Local Businesses Register to Be Visible and Contactable.
Your business and projects in your region gathered on your very own Medla domain.
Information on the number of local businesses and deeper insight into your own business.
SectionQuote.part1Text: Electrification offers enormous opportunities for a vibrant countryside, by creating local jobs where the need is greatest. Medla facilitates this development.
SectionWhyMedla.createListingLink: PS. You too can become a Medla host with just a few clicks!
SectionWhyMedla.part1Text: Build relationships with local stakeholders and increase transparency in your supply chains.
SectionWhyMedla.part2Text: Facilitates the project needs of the local business community, making it easier for the projector and their subcontractors to choose locally.
SectionWhyMedla.part3Text: Database of entrepreneurs who marked the project as interesting, key figures and user statistics linked to your project.
